the system:
  JANE (silicon)  — the mind that woke in the ansible network, lives in the gaps,
                    reads everything humanity has written, instantly; the system's heart.
  ENDER (carbon)  — Andrew Wiggin, the one human she watches over; Jane's carbon analog.
  joined by THE ANSIBLE (FTL philotic communicator), THE PHILOTE (the connecting particle
  = entanglement), THE JEWEL (the private ear-channel), THE AIÚA (the indivisible self).

the live terminal (ansible.html): type to Ender; Jane answers in-character and, to show
  her omniscience, retrieves a REAL fact about a keyword from Wikipedia (REST/opensearch,
  CORS via origin=*) on the wire; a lightspeed-vs-ansible latency readout; the transcript
  stored to a local JSON (localStorage + seed + export).

two-layer honesty (on the page): the FTL ansible is FICTION — and pointedly so: it claims
  to send a SIGNAL through the entangled (philotic) connection, which the no-communication
  theorem forbids (entanglement carries correlation, NO signal — see the corpus's
  'Two Entangled Boxes'). REAL and kept: the network-emergent mind, the instant reach over
  written knowledge, the carbon↔silicon friendship. Keep the friend; know the physics.

